creator: Randstad NV
descriptionHtml:
Note: In order to use the “my Tempo Team” app you must be actively engaged with Tempo Team. The set of features might differ per user. If you think that you are missing a feature contact your Tempo Team consultant.

Not part of Tempo Team? Visit a branch or register online to become a part of Tempo Team. Need login credentials? Please contact your Tempo Team Consultant.

With the “my Tempo Team” app, you can do all of the following directly from your phone, instead of having to get in touch with your consultant or branch:

Availability
• Easily set and adjust when you are available or unavailable to work (entire days, or part of the day)
• Your consultant will always be up to date with your availability, no need to call or go to the branch

Availability
• Easily set and adjust when you are available or unavailable to work (entire days, or part of the day)
• Your consultant will always be up to date with your availability, no need to call or go to the branch

Scheduling
• Receive planned shifts and accept or reject them
• Apply to open shifts
• Cancel a shift when you are not able to make it

Time off
• Easily request vacation days or report sick
• View your vacation balance and the status of requests

Documents
• View and download copies of your payslips, contracts and other documents

Punch Clock
• Easily record the start and end time of your shift

News center
• Receive updates and useful information from Tempo Team and your employer
• Regularly updated content, including tips and tricks
• Useful articles that can help you progress in your career

The set of features might differ per user. If you think that you are missing a feature contact your Tempo Team consultant.

appDetails.recentChangesHtml:
We' are bringing improvements across the app. From shifts to the calendar to accessibility, we worked on all features to make the app better and more robust.
In this version:
- You can now see password-protected documents in the app
- You'll be informed that you're not using the latest version of the app
- We are introducing a new actions button, check it out in the calendar and when managing alerts
- Accessibility improvements to work better with screen readers

With the “my Tempo Team” app, you can do all of the following directly from your phone, instead of having to get in touch with your consultant or branch:

Availability
• Easily set and adjust when you are available or unavailable to work (entire days, or part of the day)
• Your consultant will always be up to date with your availability, no need to call or go to the branch

Availability
• Easily set and adjust when you are available or unavailable to work (entire days, or part of the day)
• Your consultant will always be up to date with your availability, no need to call or go to the branch

Scheduling
• Receive planned shifts and accept or reject them
• Apply to open shifts
• Cancel a shift when you are not able to make it

Time off
• Easily request vacation days or report sick
• View your vacation balance and the status of requests

Documents
• View and download copies of your payslips, contracts and other documents

Punch Clock
• Easily record the start and end time of your shift

News center
• Receive updates and useful information from Tempo Team and your employer
• Regularly updated content, including tips and tricks
• Useful articles that can help you progress in your career

The set of features might differ per user. If you think that you are missing a feature contact your Tempo Team consultant.
